# -D after real rules have been loaded discards them.
# grounding: auditctl(8) -D deletes ALL existing kernel audit rules. When -D appears
# after rules that have already been loaded in the stream, those rules are discarded.
# The standard pattern is -D at the top of the FIRST file; here it appears mid-stream.
# au-W04 fires at this -D rule, naming the count of discarded rules before it.
-D
-a always,exit -S mount -k mount_after_D
